          <p>Hospitable (formerly Smartbnb) consistently tops the list for independent hosts managing a small portfolio. Its automated messaging is genuinely impressive: you can set up rule-based templates that send the right message at the right time, customized with guest names, check-in codes, and property-specific details. The platform also generates a direct booking website for each property, which lets you capture repeat guests without paying Airbnb's service fees.</p>

          <p>Smart lock integrations with Yale, Schlage, and other major brands make it easy to send unique door codes automatically upon booking confirmation. For a solo host or small operator, Hospitable handles 80% of the daily work that would otherwise consume several hours each week.</p>

          <h3>Hostaway: Best for Growing Portfolios</h3>
          <p>Once you cross five or more properties, Hostaway's enterprise features justify the higher price. The owner portal lets you share reporting with property owners if you're running a co-hosting operation. Its channel manager connects to over 100 booking platforms, and the analytics dashboard gives you a clear picture of performance across your entire portfolio. Hostaway also integrates with more third-party tools than most PMS options.</p>

          <h3>Guesty: Enterprise Power at Mid-Market Price</h3>
          <p>Guesty occupies the middle ground between Hospitable and Hostaway. The unified inbox consolidates messages from Airbnb, VRBO, Booking.com, and direct bookings into one view, which is invaluable once you're managing multiple platforms. Its task management feature lets you assign, track, and verify cleaning and maintenance jobs directly within the platform.</p>

